  Year                     = {2014},
  Number                   = {4},
  Pages                    = {045901},
  Volume                   = {26},

  Abstract                 = {Resonant ultrasound spectroscopy has been used to measure the elastic and anelastic behaviour through known structural and magnetic phase transitions in single crystal hexagonal YMnO 3 . Anomalous elastic behaviour is observed at the high temperature structural transition at ∼1260 K, with a discontinuity in the elastic constants and nonlinear recovery below T c , consistent with ##IMG## [http://ej.iop.org/images/0953-8984/26/4/045901/cm487966ieqn54.gif] {$\lambda e{Q}_{\mathrm{s}}^{2}$} coupling. There is no change in dissipation associated with this high temperature transition, and no evidence in the elastic or anelastic behaviour for any secondary transition at ∼920 K, thus supporting the thesis of a single high temperature transformation. Elastic stiffening is observed on cooling through T N , in accordance with previous studies, and the excess elastic constant appears to scale with the square of the magnetic order parameter. The strains incurred at T N are a factor of ∼20 smaller than those at the structural transition, implying very weak ##IMG## [http://ej.iop.org/images/0953-8984/26/4/045901/cm487966ieqn59.gif] {$\lambda e{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}^{2}$} coupling and a dominant contribution to the variation in the elastic constants from ##IMG## [http://ej.iop.org/images/0953-8984/26/4/045901/cm487966ieqn60.gif] {$\lambda {e}^{2}{Q}_{\mathrm{m}}^{2}$} . The increased acoustic dissipation above T N is consistent with an order–disorder process.},
